<div class="quotetitle">pragma wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I did my homework on this.  I'm not 100% sure on the dimensions, but this looks like the right connector for a GamePak:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.mouser.com/index.cfm?handler=displayproduct&amp;lstdispproductid=473351&amp;e_categoryid=50&amp;e_pcodeid=58700" class="postlink">EDAC 72P cartridge connector</a><br /><br />At least they ship in (somewhat) discrete quantities.  The price could be lower, but its worth not having to hack ISA or Floppy connectors all afternoon.<br /></div><br /><br />Sorry, but that's no good. The pin pitch is listed as 0.125" (3.18mm), which is WAY too wide for an NES cartridge, whose pitch is 2.50mm.<br /><br />They do have a 60-pin cart edge connector which has 0.100" (2.54mm) pitch, the correct spacing for a Famicom cartridge. However, it is designed for board thicknesses between 0.054" and 0.070"; Famicom cartridge boards are 0.043" thick, so they would fit extremely loosely and might not make consistent contact.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Mar 01, 2006 11:31 am</p><hr />
